vectorData.altText: That's right! The vascular pole is identifiable by the presence of vessels filled with RBCs.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Depicted is the vascular pole (VP) where the afferent/efferent arteriole enter/exit the glomerulus (G). The urinary pole (UP) is where the ultrafiltrate exits Bowman’s space and enters the PCT (simple cuboidal epithelium). Macula densa (MD), tightly packed columnar cells where the distal tubule contacts the afferent arteriole at the vascular pole.
Histological image of a renal corpuscle.
